  "texts": [
    "This is one of the first works to use LLMs as decentralized behavioral engines for non-human and non-verbal, swarm-like agents.",
    "We demonstrate our framework on two classical swarm intelligence scenarios-ant colony foraging and bird flocking-each involving different sensory inputs and emergent outcomes.",
    "In both cases, agents receive localized information about their environment and act based on LLM-generated decisions.",
    "(2) We introduce a generalizable toolchain for integrating LLMs with OpenAI's GPT models via Python, enabling agents to act based on prompt-generated decisions rather than fixed procedural logic.",
    "This framework decouples agent logic from hardcoded rules, enabling behavior to be modified or extended via natural language prompts."
  ],
